From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 7 Feb 2026 22:11:07 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: ACPI: Suppress cosmetic warnings on CIX Sky1 ACPI boot
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

On ACPI-only systems with CIX Sky1 SoC, two harmless warnings appear
during PCI enumeration:

1. "of_root node is NULL" from PCI OF bridge node creation — expected
   on ACPI systems where there is no device tree. Silence the error
   and return quietly when !of_root, since the DT overlay path is
   simply not applicable.

2. CIXH2020 platform device creation fails with -EBUSY because the
   PCIe controller register regions overlap with PCI root bridge
   resources. These vendor ACPI devices (Cadence PCIe controllers)
   are not needed as platform devices — firmware already initializes
   the hardware, and PCI enumeration proceeds via the PNP0A08 root
   bridges. Add CIXH2020 to the forbidden_id_list to prevent
   unnecessary platform device creation attempts.
---
 drivers/acpi/acpi_platform.c | 1 +
 drivers/pci/of.c             | 6 ++----
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/acpi/acpi_platform.c b/drivers/acpi/acpi_platform.c
index 48d15dd785f6e..7631935ba2ae4 100644
--- a/drivers/acpi/acpi_platform.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/acpi_platform.c
@@ -30,6 +30,7 @@ static const struct acpi_device_id forbidden_id_list[] = {
 	{"PNP0100",  0},	/* Timer */
 	{"PNP0200",  0},	/* AT DMA Controller */
 	{ACPI_SMBUS_MS_HID,  ACPI_ALLOW_WO_RESOURCES},	/* ACPI SMBUS virtual device */
+	{"CIXH2020", 0},	/* CIX Sky1 PCIe controller (handled via PNP0A08) */
 	{ }
 };
 
diff --git a/drivers/pci/of.c b/drivers/pci/of.c
index 3579265f11984..cf54a54f27091 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/of.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/of.c
@@ -773,11 +773,9 @@ void of_pci_make_host_bridge_node(struct pci_host_bridge *bridge)
 		return;
 	}
 
-	/* Check if there is a DT root node to attach the created node */
-	if (!of_root) {
-		pr_err("of_root node is NULL, cannot create PCI host bridge node\n");
+	/* On ACPI systems there is no DT root — this is expected */
+	if (!of_root)
 		return;
-	}
 
 	name = kasprintf(GFP_KERNEL, "pci@%x,%x", pci_domain_nr(bridge->bus),
 			 bridge->bus->number);
